If you don't want to modify the Jenkinsfile, you can add parameters from the Jenkins UI:

Open the job.
Click Configure.
Check This project is parameterized (Freestyle) or go to General → This project is parameterized (Pipeline job).
Add a parameter:
String Parameter → name it BRANCH_NAME
or Choice Parameter → provide a list of branches.
Save.

After saving, Jenkins will show Build with Parameters.

However, the parameter by itself does nothing. The SCM configuration or Jenkinsfile must actually use ${BRANCH_NAME}.

For a Pipeline job configured through the UI:

In Pipeline Script from SCM → Branch Specifier, use:

*/${BRANCH_NAME}

For a Freestyle job:

In Source Code Management → Git → Branches to build, use:

*/${BRANCH_NAME}

Then when you click Build with Parameters, you can enter main, develop, feature/test, etc., and Jenkins will build that branch.

